This paper deals with interpreting intermediate layers in neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also proposes modifications to improve the effectiveness and robustness of the interpretation, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper uses natural language processing techniques to analyze text data, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
